Hi there! To write an if/then statement in C, you can use the following syntax:

if (condition) {
  // Code to execute if the condition is true
} else {
  // Code to execute if the condition is false
}

For example, you can use an if/then statement to check if a variable is greater than 0 and execute different code depending on the result:

int x = 5;

if (x > 0) {
  // Code to execute if x is greater than 0
} else {
  // Code to execute if x is not greater than 0
}

